hopobject.body: Cool site goodluck :) buyedmedsgeneric03.com The international community – which has pledged $4 billion in aid – believes assistance should not be granted to "illegitimate" governments unsanctioned by free and fair voting. But this approach focuses too much on the process of elections rather than their substance – that is, on what elections should achieve for the Malian people. It also reinforces the view that what Mali needs is massive foreign aid. For Mali to succeed, such aid may be necessary, but it is hardly sufficient.
